def is_prime(n):
    if n < 2:
        return False
    for i in range(2, int(n**0.5) + 1):
        if n % i == 0:
            return False
    return True

xs = [3, 7, 11, 13, 17, 19, 23]
prime_count = sum(1 for x in xs if is_prime(x))
print(prime_count)
```
The most common arithmetic mistake on this is forgetting to check if a number is divisible by any number up to its square root, rather than checking all the way up to the number itself.
